    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required gradation levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is partially mitigated by the medium model influence level and the fact that ASTM F1717 specifies a single canonical test condition. All three QoIs satisfy the quantitative acceptance criterion (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%). The FEA framework is accepted for predicting ASTM F1717 compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
